
"smart_sources:notes/0.8/2025-03-13/073729-happiness-inner.md": {"path":"notes/0.8/2025-03-13/073729-happiness-inner.md","last_embed":{"hash":null},"embeddings":{},"last_read":{"hash":"6a0752242b500d53e2d3b89c797b1f9e65804782699b80248dea13b2643850ca","at":1743481010662},"class_name":"SmartSource","outlinks":[],"metadata":{"robots":"By accessing this content, you agree to https://qnfo.org/LICENSE. Non-commercial use only. Attribution required.","DC.rights":"https://qnfo.org/LICENSE. Users are bound by terms upon access.","author":"Rowan Brad Quni","email":"rowan.quni@qnfo.org","website":"http://qnfo.org","LinkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/rowan-quni-868006341","ORCID":"https://orcid.org/0009-0002-4317-5604","tags":"QNFO, AI, ArtificialIntelligence, artificial intelligence, quantum, physics, science, Einstein, QuantumMechanics, quantum mechanics, QuantumComputing, quantum computing, information, InformationTheory, information theory, InformationalUniverse, informational universe, informational universe hypothesis, IUH, LLM, User, Gemini","created":"2024-11-13T19:54:01Z","modified":"2025-03-13T01:03:45Z"},"blocks":{"#---frontmatter---":[1,12],"#LLM":[14,15],"#User : We surround ourselves with the comforts of material things and possession but when the mind is clear we need nothing we are the monks who own but three robes a razor and the thread we do not need to give offerings we do not need to buy anything because our happiness is already assured.":[16,17],"#Gemini : This passage reflects a core tenet of many spiritual traditions, particularly Buddhism. It highlights the idea that true happiness isn’t derived from external possessions but from inner peace and clarity. Material comforts, while perhaps offering temporary pleasure, can ultimately distract from this inner work and create a cycle of wanting and needing. The image of the monk with only essential possessions symbolizes detachment from material desires and a focus on cultivating contentment within. The passage suggests that when the mind is free from the clutter of desires, true happiness, which is already inherent within us, can be realized. It’s not about acquiring things but about removing the obstacles that prevent us from experiencing our innate joy.":[18,19],"#Gemini :":[20,21]},"last_import":{"mtime":1741827825074,"size":1868,"at":1743481010662,"hash":"6a0752242b500d53e2d3b89c797b1f9e65804782699b80248dea13b2643850ca"}},